{"lemma":"رَبِيبَيْ","slug":"رَبِيبَيْ","root":"ر.ب.ب","root_slug":"ر-ب-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ب-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n14380"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%A8%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n14380","headword_ar":"رَبِيبٌ","root":"rb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Reared, fostered, brought up, fed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nourished;"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and taken good care of, until the age of puberty;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see 1;)] as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marobuwbN","text_ar":"مَرْبُوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, K;) both applied to a boy: (S, M:) and in like manner applied to a horse: (M:) or the latter epithet, applied to a horse, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tended well,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taken good care of:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) the former is also applied to a gazelle; (IAar, K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dxl","text_ar":"دخل"},{"kind":"text","text":";) [as meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brought up in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"near, the house"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tent, and there fed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aholiY~N","text_ar":"اَهْلِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA in that art.:) and [its fem.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiybapN","text_ar":"رَبِيبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to a ewe or she-goat, ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aApN","text_ar":"شَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", K,) meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brought up in the tent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"house, for the sake of her milk;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K; [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rub~aY","text_ar":"رُبَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":";]) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaAy^ibu","text_ar":"رَبَايِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) this last being applied to sheep or goats"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that are tied near to the tents,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"houses, and there fed, and that do not go forth to pasture;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA;) of which it is said that none are to be taken for the poor-rate. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A step-son,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] a man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wife's son"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, A, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by another husband;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, A, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabuwbN","text_ar":"رَبُوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arib~aA='u","text_ar":"اَرِبَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiybapN","text_ar":"رَبِيبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A step-daughter;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] a woman's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"husband's daughter by another wife:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or a man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wife's daughter"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, A, Mgh, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by another husband;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, A;) because he rears her: (Mgh:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaAy^ibu","text_ar":"رَبَايِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Mgh, Msb) and sometimes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiybaAtN","text_ar":"رَبِيبَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b3-  Also, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAb~N","text_ar":"رَابٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M, K,) both syn., like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ahiydN","text_ar":"شَهِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAhidN","text_ar":"شَاهِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabiyrN","text_ar":"خَبِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAbirN","text_ar":"خَابِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) or the latter, (T, S,) mentioned by IAar, is the correct term, (T,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A step-father;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"husband of a mother"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who has a child by another husband."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiybapN","text_ar":"رَبِيبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAb~apN","text_ar":"رَابَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T,) or the latter [only], (S, K,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A stepmother;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wife of a father"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who has a child by another wife."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiybapN","text_ar":"رَبِيبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A foster-mother;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a woman who has the charge of a child, who carries him, and takes care of him, and rears,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fosters, him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, S, M, Msb, K;) like ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAb~apN","text_ar":"رَابَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the former being of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEilaypN","text_ar":"فَعِلَيةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAEilapN","text_ar":"فَاعِلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arb~aA='u Aln~abiY~","text_ar":"اَربَّا=ءُ النَّبِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The foster-fathers of the Prophet"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is an appellation given to the people [of the tribe of Saad] among whom Mohammad was suckled; as though"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Arb~A='","text_ar":"اربّا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"were pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiybN","text_ar":"رَبِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as it is said to be in one of the senses mentioned above]. (TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiybN","text_ar":"رَبِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A confederate; a person with whom one unites in a confederacy, league,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"covenant."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A king."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.)"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1006}],"source_refs":["S","M","A","T","Msb","K","Mgh","TA"]}]}}